Reasoning: 
1. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper proposes a new method for calculating characteristics of complex networks, specifically sparse networks with cause-effect character. The paper also discusses the semantic interpretation of the proposed characteristics of concept nodes, which can be related to social networks. 
2. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The Kirchhoff rules used in the proposed method are commonly used in systems and control theory. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the computational simplicity of the proposed K-method, which can be related to data structures and algorithms. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The proposed method can be applied to cognitive maps, which are used in artificial intelligence for representing knowledge. 
5. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes new characteristics of concept nodes, which can be related to machine learning and data analysis.
